hopobject.body: I love this site scorpiopharm.com Nasr Allah Zakaria, Jessi's uncle, said that members of the family were focusing on achieving what little justice they can for their "beautiful girl". Jessi's father told the BBC: "Jessi was everything to us. Her killers didn't know that Jessi was my life my future. They killed our future. I lived for her." The family will visit the office of Cairo's central prosecutor, hoping that Jessi's case will receive a better response than the silence that has so far followed the murder.
